induces a large number of\nmechanical states at the specimen surface. The induced heterogeneity is\ngenerally analysed through the distribution of the biaxiality ratio and the\nmaximal eigen value of the strain. The Digital Image Correlation (DIC)\ntechnique is generally used to retrieve the different mechanical states\ninduces, and provides the full kinematic field at the specimen surface, i.e. a\nlarge number of experimental data to be analysed to identify the constitutive\nparameters of the behaviour model considered.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Jul 2019 06:29:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-08"}
